## Source-Specific Playbooks

### Playbook A: FINRA Short Sale Volume

```
Gate 1 — PROBE:
  URL: cdn.finra.org/equity/regsho/daily/CNMSshvol{YYYYMMDD}.txt
  Format: Pipe-delimited text
  Auth: None
  Rate limits: None known (it's static files)
  Size: ~2MB per day × 252 trading days = ~500MB/year
  Schema: Date|Symbol|ShortVolume|ShortExemptVolume|TotalVolume|Market

Gate 2 — SAMPLE:
  Download ONE day: yesterday's file
  Check: Does SPY row exist? Is short_volume numeric? Is total_volume > 0?

Gate 3 — CLEAN:
  Parse pipe delimiter
  Filter to our tickers: SPY, QQQ, AAPL, TSLA, NVDA, IWM
  Compute: short_volume_pct = short_volume / total_volume * 100
  Drop rows where total_volume = 0

Gate 4 — STORE:
  data/external/finra_short/raw/CNMS_{date}.txt  (original)
  data/external/finra_short/clean/short_vol_{date}.parquet
  data/external/finra_short/db/finra_short.db → table: daily_short_volume

Gate 5 — VERIFY:
  For yesterday: compare our short_volume_pct(SPY) vs Stockgrid's value
  Tolerance: ±2 percentage points
  If mismatch > 2pp: investigate before loading more days
```

### Playbook B: CFTC COT Archives

```
Gate 1 — PROBE:
  URL: cftc.gov/files/dea/history/deacot{YEAR}.zip
  Format: CSV inside ZIP
  Auth: None
  Size: ~20MB/year compressed
  Schema: 100+ columns including Market_and_Exchange_Names,
          NonComm_Positions_Long_All, NonComm_Positions_Short_All, etc.
  Python lib: cot_reports (pip install cot_reports)

Gate 2 — SAMPLE:
  Use cot_reports lib to fetch current year only
  Filter to our 6 contracts: ES, NQ, TY, GC, CL, VX
  Check: Do specs_net / comm_net values look reasonable? (±1M range)

Gate 3 — CLEAN:
  Map CFTC contract names to our short keys (ES, NQ, etc.)
  Extract: report_date, specs_long, specs_short, specs_net, comm_long, comm_short, comm_net, open_interest
  Compute: specs_ratio = specs_net / open_interest
  Drop duplicate report dates

Gate 4 — STORE:
  data/external/cftc_cot/raw/deacot{YEAR}.csv
  data/external/cftc_cot/clean/cot_positioning.parquet
  data/external/cftc_cot/db/cot_history.db → table: weekly_positioning

Gate 5 — VERIFY:
  Compare latest week's specs_net for ES vs our /cot/positioning API
  Must be EXACT match (same source data)
  If mismatch: our parser has a bug — fix before loading history
```

### Playbook C: Kaggle SPY Options Chains

```
Gate 1 — PROBE:
  URL: kaggle.com/datasets/kylegraupe/spy-daily-eod-options-quotes-2020-2024
  Format: CSV (possibly multiple files)
  Auth: Kaggle API token
  Size: ~2-5GB compressed
  Schema: underlying, expiry, type, strike, bid, ask, volume, open_interest,
          implied_vol, delta, gamma, theta, vega
  ⚠️ LARGE — needs chunking strategy

Gate 2 — SAMPLE:
  Download metadata only first (kaggle datasets info)
  Then download ONE file or filter to ONE trading day
  Check: SPY has ≥500 option contracts per day? Greeks are populated?

Gate 3 — CLEAN:
  Filter to SPY only (if multi-ticker)
  Parse expiry dates to standard format
  Compute per-strike GEX = gamma × open_interest × 100 × spot²
  Aggregate: total_gex = sum(call_gex) - sum(put_gex)
  Classify: POSITIVE if total_gex > 0, NEGATIVE if < 0

Gate 4 — STORE:
  data/external/kaggle_options/raw/  (original CSVs, DO NOT modify)
  data/external/kaggle_options/clean/spy_options_{date}.parquet
  data/external/kaggle_options/db/gex_history.db → table: daily_gex
    Columns: date, total_gex, regime, gamma_flip, max_pain, top_walls_json

Gate 5 — VERIFY:
  For any date in the dataset: independently compute RSI from yfinance prices
  Compare day's GEX regime to next-day realized volatility
  Does NEGATIVE gamma → higher abs(daily_return)?
  This is the CORE THESIS test — if it fails, our entire gamma theory is wrong
```

