## Execution Order

Do NOT parallelize data downloads. Process ONE source at a time, all 5 gates:

```
1. yfinance prices       (smallest, fastest, foundation for all others)
2. FINRA short volume     (one HTTP GET per day, simple schema)
3. CFTC COT               (existing Python lib, small dataset)
4. FRED economic           (API with lib, small dataset)
5. CBOE VIX futures        (simple CSVs)
6. Kaggle options chains   (LAST — largest, most complex, needs all others for verification)
```

**Why this order?** Each source VERIFIES against previous ones:
- FINRA verifies against our Stockgrid (which uses yfinance prices)
- COT verifies against our existing COT endpoint
- FRED fills gaps in our economic DB (which needs yfinance for SPY changes)
- VIX futures verify against yfinance ^VIX
- Kaggle options need prices (yfinance) + VIX for GEX computation

