## Failure Modes & Recovery

| Failure | What to do |
|---------|-----------|
| Gate 2 sample has wrong schema | STOP. Re-read docs. Schema may have changed. |
| Gate 3 cleaning produces > 5% dropped rows | Investigate BEFORE proceeding. Why so much bad data? |
| Gate 5 verification < 95% match | DO NOT use dataset. Fix parser or find alternative source. |
| Download interrupted mid-file | Delete partial file. Re-download from scratch. Never resume into corrupted file. |
| Rate limited | Add exponential backoff. Never retry more than 3x. |
| Disk space concern | Check `df -h` BEFORE starting large downloads. |

---

## Golden Rules

1. **Sample before bulk** — 10 rows before 10 million
2. **Raw is sacred** — never modify files in `raw/`
3. **Clean is reproducible** — delete `clean/` and regenerate from `raw/`
4. **Verify against independent truth** — not against yourself
5. **Manifest everything** — if it's not in manifest.json, it didn't happen
6. **One source at a time** — finish all 5 gates before starting the next source
7. **Fail loud, fail fast** — a ValueError is better than silently wrong data
